verses.text_plain: Moreover the word of the Lord came to me, saying,
verses.verse_html: 1Moreover the word of the Lord came to me, saying,

verses.text_plain: Go and cry in the ears of Jerusalem, saying, Thus saith the Lord; I remember thee, the kindness of thy youth, the love of thine espousals, when thou wentest after me in the wilderness, in a land that was not sown.
verses.verse_html:
2Go and cry in the ears of Jerusalem, saying, Thus saith the Lord; I remember thee, the kindness of thy youth, the love of thine espousals, when thou wentest after me in the wilderness, in a land that was not sown. ▼
▼ thee: or, for thy sake

footnotes.body_html: ▼ thee: or, for thy sake

verses.text_plain: Israel was holiness unto the Lord, and the firstfruits of his increase: all that devour him shall offend; evil shall come upon them, saith the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 3Israel was holiness unto the Lord, and the firstfruits of his increase: all that devour him shall offend; evil shall come upon them, saith the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Hear ye the word of the Lord, O house of Jacob, and all the families of the house of Israel:
verses.verse_html: 4Hear ye the word of the Lord, O house of Jacob, and all the families of the house of Israel:

verses.text_plain: Thus saith the Lord, What iniquity have your fathers found in me, that they are gone far from me, and have walked after vanity, and are become vain?
verses.verse_html: 5Thus saith the Lord, What iniquity have your fathers found in me, that they are gone far from me, and have walked after vanity, and are become vain?

tokens.text: in me, that they are gone far

verses.text_plain: Neither said they, Where is the Lord that brought us up out of the land of Egypt, that led us through the wilderness, through a land of deserts and of pits, through a land of drought, and of the shadow of death, through a land that no man passed through, and where no man dwelt?
verses.verse_html: 6Neither said they, Where is the Lord that brought us up out of the land of Egypt, that led us through the wilderness, through a land of deserts and of pits, through a land of drought, and of the shadow of death, through a land that no man passed through, and where no man dwelt?

tokens.text: and of the shadow of death

verses.text_plain: And I brought you into a plentiful country, to eat the fruit thereof and the goodness thereof; but when ye entered, ye defiled my land, and made mine heritage an abomination.
verses.verse_html:
7And I brought you into a plentiful country, to eat the fruit thereof and the goodness thereof; but when ye entered, ye defiled my land, and made mine heritage an abomination. ▼
▼ a plentiful…: or, the land of Carmel

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a plentiful…: or, the land of Carmel
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a plentiful…: or, the land of Carmel

verses.text_plain: The priests said not, Where is the Lord? and they that handle the law knew me not: the pastors also transgressed against me, and the prophets prophesied by Baal, and walked after things that do not profit.
verses.verse_html: 8The priests said not, Where is the Lord? and they that handle the law knew me not: the pastors also transgressed against me, and the prophets prophesied by Baal, and walked after things that do not profit.

verses.text_plain: Wherefore I will yet plead with you, saith the Lord, and with your children’s children will I plead.
verses.verse_html: 9Wherefore I will yet plead with you, saith the Lord, and with your children’s children will I plead.

verses.text_plain: For pass over the isles of Chittim, and see; and send unto Kedar, and consider diligently, and see if there be such a thing.
verses.verse_html:
10For pass over the isles of Chittim, and see; and send unto Kedar, and consider diligently, and see if there be such a thing. ▼
▼ over: or, over to

footnotes.body_html: ▼ over: or, over to

verses.text_plain: Hath a nation changed their gods, which are yet no gods? but my people have changed their glory for that which doth not profit.
verses.verse_html: 11Hath a nation changed their gods, which are yet no gods? but my people have changed their glory for that which doth not profit.

verses.text_plain: Be astonished, O ye heavens, at this, and be horribly afraid, be ye very desolate, saith the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 12Be astonished, O ye heavens, at this, and be horribly afraid, be ye very desolate, saith the Lord.

tokens.text: at this, and be horribly afraid

verses.text_plain: For my people have committed two evils; they have forsaken me the fountain of living waters, and hewed them out cisterns, broken cisterns, that can hold no water.
verses.verse_html: 13For my people have committed two evils; they have forsaken me the fountain of living waters, and hewed them out cisterns, broken cisterns, that can hold no water.

verses.text_plain: Is Israel a servant? is he a homeborn slave? why is he spoiled?
verses.verse_html:
14Is Israel a servant? is he a homeborn slave? why is he spoiled? ▼
▼ spoiled: Heb. become a spoil?

footnotes.body_html: ▼ spoiled: Heb. become a spoil?

verses.text_plain: The young lions roared upon him, and yelled, and they made his land waste: his cities are burned without inhabitant.
verses.verse_html:
15The young lions roared upon him, and yelled, and they made his land waste: his cities are burned without inhabitant. ▼
▼ yelled: Heb. gave out their voice

footnotes.body_text: ▼ yelled: Heb. gave out their voice
footnotes.body_html: ▼ yelled: Heb. gave out their voice

verses.text_plain: Also the children of Noph and Tahapanes have broken the crown of thy head.
verses.verse_html:
16Also the children of Noph and Tahapanes have broken the crown of thy head. ▼
▼ have…: or, feed on thy crown

footnotes.body_text: ▼ have…: or, feed on thy crown
footnotes.body_html: ▼ have…: or, feed on thy crown

verses.text_plain: Hast thou not procured this unto thyself, in that thou hast forsaken the Lord thy God, when he led thee by the way?
verses.verse_html: 17Hast thou not procured this unto thyself, in that thou hast forsaken the Lord thy God, when he led thee by the way?

tokens.text: this unto thyself, in that thou hast forsaken

verses.text_plain: And now what hast thou to do in the way of Egypt, to drink the waters of Sihor? or what hast thou to do in the way of Assyria, to drink the waters of the river?
verses.verse_html: 18And now what hast thou to do in the way of Egypt, to drink the waters of Sihor? or what hast thou to do in the way of Assyria, to drink the waters of the river?

tokens.text: And now what hast thou to do in the way
or what hast thou to do in the way

verses.text_plain: Thine own wickedness shall correct thee, and thy backslidings shall reprove thee: know therefore and see that it is an evil thing and bitter, that thou hast forsaken the Lord thy God, and that my fear is not in thee, saith the Lord God of hosts.
verses.verse_html: 19Thine own wickedness shall correct thee, and thy backslidings shall reprove thee: know therefore and see that it is an evil thing and bitter, that thou hast forsaken the Lord thy God, and that my fear is not in thee, saith the Lord God of hosts.

verses.text_plain: For of old time I have broken thy yoke, and burst thy bands; and thou saidst, I will not transgress; when upon every high hill and under every green tree thou wanderest, playing the harlot.
verses.verse_html:
20For of old time I have broken thy yoke, and burst thy bands; and thou saidst, I will not transgress; when upon every high hill and under every green tree thou wanderest, playing the harlot. ▼
▼ transgress: or, serve

verses.text_plain: Yet I had planted thee a noble vine, wholly a right seed: how then art thou turned into the degenerate plant of a strange vine unto me?
verses.verse_html: 21Yet I had planted thee a noble vine, wholly a right seed: how then art thou turned into the degenerate plant of a strange vine unto me?

verses.text_plain: For though thou wash thee with nitre, and take thee much soap, yet thine iniquity is marked before me, saith the Lord God.
verses.verse_html: 22For though thou wash thee with nitre, and take thee much soap, yet thine iniquity is marked before me, saith the Lord God.

verses.text_plain: How canst thou say, I am not polluted, I have not gone after Baalim? see thy way in the valley, know what thou hast done: thou art a swift dromedary traversing her ways;
verses.verse_html:
23How canst thou say, I am not polluted, I have not gone after Baalim? see thy way in the valley, know what thou hast done: thou art a swift dromedary traversing her ways; ▼
▼ thou art…: or, O swift dromedary

footnotes.body_text: ▼ thou art…: or, O swift dromedary
footnotes.body_html: ▼ thou art…: or, O swift dromedary

verses.text_plain: A wild ass used to the wilderness, that snuffeth up the wind at her pleasure; in her occasion who can turn her away? all they that seek her will not weary themselves; in her month they shall find her.
verses.verse_html:
24A wild ass used to the wilderness, that snuffeth up the wind at her pleasure; in her occasion who can turn her away? all they that seek her will not weary themselves; in her month they shall find her. ▼
▼ A wild…: or, O wild ass, etc
 , ▼
▼ used: Heb. taught
 , ▼
▼ her pleasure: Heb. the desire of her heart
 , ▼
▼ turn…: or, reverse it?

footnotes.body_text: ▼ A wild…: or, O wild ass, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ A wild…: or, O wild ass, etc

footnotes.body_text: ▼ her pleasure: Heb. the desire of her heart
footnotes.body_html: ▼ her pleasure: Heb. the desire of her heart
▼ turn…: or, reverse it?

verses.text_plain: Withhold thy foot from being unshod, and thy throat from thirst: but thou saidst, There is no hope: no; for I have loved strangers, and after them will I go.
verses.verse_html:
25Withhold thy foot from being unshod, and thy throat from thirst: but thou saidst, There is no hope: no; for I have loved strangers, and after them will I go. ▼
▼ There…: or, Is the case desperate?

footnotes.body_text: ▼ There…: or, Is the case desperate?
footnotes.body_html: ▼ There…: or, Is the case desperate?

verses.text_plain: As the thief is ashamed when he is found, so is the house of Israel ashamed; they, their kings, their princes, and their priests, and their prophets,
verses.verse_html: 26As the thief is ashamed when he is found, so is the house of Israel ashamed; they, their kings, their princes, and their priests, and their prophets,

verses.text_plain: Saying to a stock, Thou art my father; and to a stone, Thou hast brought me forth: for they have turned their back unto me, and not their face: but in the time of their trouble they will say, Arise, and save us.
verses.verse_html:
27Saying to a stock, Thou art my father; and to a stone, Thou hast brought me forth: for they have turned their back unto me, and not their face: but in the time of their trouble they will say, Arise, and save us. ▼
▼ brought…: or, begotten me
 , ▼
▼ their back: Heb. the hinder part of the neck

footnotes.body_html: ▼ brought…: or, begotten me

footnotes.body_text: ▼ their back: Heb. the hinder part of the neck
footnotes.body_html: ▼ their back: Heb. the hinder part of the neck

verses.text_plain: But where are thy gods that thou hast made thee? let them arise, if they can save thee in the time of thy trouble: for according to the number of thy cities are thy gods, O Judah.
verses.verse_html:
28But where are thy gods that thou hast made thee? let them arise, if they can save thee in the time of thy trouble: for according to the number of thy cities are thy gods, O Judah. ▼
▼ trouble: Heb. evil

verses.text_plain: Wherefore will ye plead with me? ye all have transgressed against me, saith the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 29Wherefore will ye plead with me? ye all have transgressed against me, saith the Lord.

tokens.text: with me? ye all have transgressed

verses.text_plain: In vain have I smitten your children; they received no correction: your own sword hath devoured your prophets, like a destroying lion.
verses.verse_html: 30In vain have I smitten your children; they received no correction: your own sword hath devoured your prophets, like a destroying lion.

verses.text_plain: O generation, see ye the word of the Lord. Have I been a wilderness unto Israel? a land of darkness? wherefore say my people, We are lords; we will come no more unto thee?
verses.verse_html:
31O generation, see ye the word of the Lord. Have I been a wilderness unto Israel? a land of darkness? wherefore say my people, We are lords; we will come no more unto thee? ▼
▼ We are…: Heb. We have dominion

footnotes.body_text: ▼ We are…: Heb. We have dominion
footnotes.body_html: ▼ We are…: Heb. We have dominion

verses.text_plain: Can a maid forget her ornaments, or a bride her attire? yet my people have forgotten me days without number.
verses.verse_html: 32Can a maid forget her ornaments, or a bride her attire? yet my people have forgotten me days without number.

verses.text_plain: Why trimmest thou thy way to seek love? therefore hast thou also taught the wicked ones thy ways.
verses.verse_html: 33Why trimmest thou thy way to seek love? therefore hast thou also taught the wicked ones thy ways.

verses.text_plain: Also in thy skirts is found the blood of the souls of the poor innocents: I have not found it by secret search, but upon all these.
verses.verse_html:
34Also in thy skirts is found the blood of the souls of the poor innocents: I have not found it by secret search, but upon all these. ▼
▼ secret…: Heb. digging

verses.text_plain: Yet thou sayest, Because I am innocent, surely his anger shall turn from me. Behold, I will plead with thee, because thou sayest, I have not sinned.
verses.verse_html: 35Yet thou sayest, Because I am innocent, surely his anger shall turn from me. Behold, I will plead with thee, because thou sayest, I have not sinned.

tokens.text: from me. Behold, I will plead

verses.text_plain: Why gaddest thou about so much to change thy way? thou also shalt be ashamed of Egypt, as thou wast ashamed of Assyria.
verses.verse_html: 36Why gaddest thou about so much to change thy way? thou also shalt be ashamed of Egypt, as thou wast ashamed of Assyria.

verses.text_plain: Yea, thou shalt go forth from him, and thine hands upon thine head: for the Lord hath rejected thy confidences, and thou shalt not prosper in them.
verses.verse_html: 37Yea, thou shalt go forth from him, and thine hands upon thine head: for the Lord hath rejected thy confidences, and thou shalt not prosper in them.
